01:24.358 --> 01:26.308
You know, with us living
together, maybe we could

01:26.310 --> 01:28.477
think about having people over.

01:28.479 --> 01:30.863
We have people
over all the time.

01:30.865 --> 01:33.532
We have the maintenance people,
the pizza delivery man...

01:34.952 --> 01:37.152
...that UPS driver
who feels the need to ask

01:37.154 --> 01:39.321
how parts of me are hanging.

01:39.323 --> 01:41.490
You know what I meant.

01:41.492 --> 01:43.125
All right, fine.

01:43.127 --> 01:44.293
Let's say that

01:44.295 --> 01:45.411
we were to entertain people.

01:45.413 --> 01:47.379
What type of gathering
did you have in mind?

01:47.381 --> 01:48.664
Huh? A meal? Lunch?

01:48.666 --> 01:49.582
Brunch? Dinner?

01:49.584 --> 01:50.833
Afternoon tea?
A formal tea? Hmm?

01:50.835 --> 01:53.302
Is it a party?
And if so, what kind of party?

01:53.304 --> 01:55.087
Is it a cocktail party?

01:55.089 --> 01:56.639
A Tupperware party?

01:56.641 --> 01:59.808
Ooh, yeah--
is it a surprise party?

01:59.810 --> 02:01.010
Oh, I hope it's not

02:01.012 --> 02:02.678
a West Coast party,
'cause according to

02:02.680 --> 02:06.315
the man on the radio,
a West Coast party don't stop.

02:06.317 --> 02:08.234
I'm sorry I mentioned it.

02:08.235 --> 02:09.852
Oh, don't be.
You get your hopes up,

02:09.854 --> 02:12.488
I knock them down.
That's called teamwork.

